<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idcfc889cf-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0" identifier="/us/usc/t48/s2170"><num value="2170">§ 2170.</num><heading> Applicable rules of procedure</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Federal Rules of Bankruptcy Procedure shall apply to a case under this subchapter and to all civil proceedings arising in or related to cases under this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idcfc889d0-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0">(<ref href="/us/pl/114/187/tIII/s310">Pub. L. 114–187, title III, § 310</ref>, <date date="2016-06-30">June 30, 2016</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/130/583">130 Stat. 583</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idcfc889d1-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idcfc889d2-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="idcfc889d3-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">The Federal Rules of Bankruptcy Procedure, referred to in text, are set out in the Appendix to Title 11, Bankruptcy.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
